Morningside Elementary School PTO is at Morningside Elementary School.
July 24 at 8:57 AM · Elizabethtown, KY ·

🏆 This summer, Dawn Corbin, Morningside’s EBD / Pass teacher, received the UK College of Education’s Teachers Who Made a Difference award. 🏆

The UK College of Education Teachers Who Made a Difference program began 22 years ago and has recognized hundreds of teachers. It is sponsored by private donations, the event was founded by Mary Ann Vimont, associate professor and director of alumni for the college.

Congratulations Ms. Corbin!!

#MESistheBest Elizabethtown Independent School District

post_text: Thank you City of Elizabethtown! What a great place to live.
shared_text:
City of Elizabethtown Government
August 4 at 8:06 AM ·

The City of Elizabethtown is proud to partner with Hardin County Schools - Kentucky and Elizabethtown Independent School District to help all of our students in Elizabethtown and Hardin County connect to the internet as they begin the new school year.

Freeman Lake Park, American Legion Park, the Nature Park as well as certain areas at Pritchard Community Center will offer free
Wi-Fi to students and families in the community.

The upcoming school year will have its challenges and the City of Elizabethtown is honored to work with our amazing school districts to help students connect.

Free Wi-Fi for students and families will be available from 8:00 am - 8:00 pm once the school year begins.

#elizabethtown #kentucky #communitypartners #hcs #eis #coe #helpingouryoungestcitizens #teamwork #ittakesavillage #teamkentucky

post_text:
If you haven't driven by the billboard on US 62 close to I-65 please do so today. The EHS 2020 graduating class and special retirees are being honored. Last day to see it!

"The memories of games, parties, and inside jokes will forever be in our heads as the class of 97. It seems like yesterday I loaned Whit Gerard a bobby pin to hold his hair back in the middle of graduation and had to explain to my parents why I cut all my hair off because I didn’t like the way it looked in my cap (true story)

But the class of 2020 didn’t get the opportunity to cultivate those memories.

So we hope that you take a moment to drive down the cul de sac or road and breathe in your success. The work is done, you did it together, and you are forever full of Panther Pride...and we promise, it never goes away. Congrats!"
~ Laura Gilbert EHS Class of '97
Thanks to Eric Hall for sponsoring as well!

It seems like yesterday I loaned Whit Gerard a bobby pin to hold his hair back in the middle of graduation and had to explain to my parents why I cut all my hair off because I didn’t like the way it looked in my cap (true story)

But the class of 2020 didn’t get the opportunity to cultivate those memories.

So we hope that you take a moment to drive down the cul de sac or road and breathe in your success. The work is done, you did it together, and you are forever full of Panther Pride...and we promise, it never goes away. Congrats!"
~ Laura Gilbert EHS Class of '97
Thanks to Eric Hall for sponsoring as well!

shared_text:
Baptist Health Hardin
March 18 at 1:38 PM ·

Today, Hardin Memorial Health (HMH) leaders announced a new hotline for people with flu-like/respiratory symptoms.

“The hotline will be staffed by HMH registered nurses who can answer questions and provide accurate information about the flu and COVID-19 symptoms,” said Shelia Smallwood, HMH Assistant Vice President, HMH Medical Group. “Callers unsure of where or when to seek treatment will be given guidance according to the latest CDC recommendations.”

Nurses will field questions and direct patients to the appropriate level of care. The hotline number is (270) 979-7777 open Monday thru Friday from 8:00 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Hotline use should be limited to those with symptoms or those with a loved one experiencing symptoms, such as a fever, cough or shortness of breath.
